==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: injectable
<hw>injectable</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>capable of being
conveniently injected; -- used of drug preparations, such as sterile
lyophilize medicine in a serum-capped vial. Opposite of
<ant>uninjectable</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Requiring injection for administration; -- of drugs,
especially those not active by oral administration. Opposite of
<contr>orally active</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Injection</ent>⟦br⟧
